\begin{frame}{Extension Constraints and Timetable Quality}
The core model focuses on feasibility, but some features affect how usable (right word?) a timetable feels.

\vspace{0.3cm}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Consecutive teaching blocks may be preferable to highly fragmented teaching, i.e rather have classes back to back than at 9am and 5pm
    \item Excessive daily contact time reduces quality
\end{itemize}

\[
\sum_{t \in T}\sum_{i \in I_k} x_{i,t,d} \leq 6
\]
\begin{itemize}
    \item This limits daily teaching load.
    \item It is a quality-based constraint, not a minimum feasibility requirement. Just because a timetable in feasible does not mean it is a good timetable
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}


