\begin{frame}{Why Start with the Vet School?}
The raw university data was large and messy. The main issues were encoded or abbreviated naming, duplicate or redundant entries, conflicting room and location indicators and event data spread across multiple weeks. So we started and focused on a smaller subset of this data: The Vet School.
\begin{itemize}
    \item The Vet School provided a smaller and more isolated subset of the university data.
    \item It has relatively little overlap with other schools and campuses.
    \item This made it a strong test case for:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Model debugging
        \item Feasibility checks
        \item Early diagnostics
        \item Sensitivity testing
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\end{frame}

